        icon: "\ud83d\udcca",
        body: "Utilization measures how busy a resource is, as a percentage:<br><br><strong>Utilization = Input Rate &divide; Capacity</strong><br><br>&bull; <strong>100%</strong> = fully busy, no idle time (this is the bottleneck)<br>&bull; <strong>50%</strong> = idle half the time<br>&bull; <strong>&gt; 100%</strong> = impossible to sustain! Work piles up.<br><br>The resource with the <em>highest utilization</em> is the bottleneck. When different amounts of work flow to different stages (e.g., due to defects), you must compare utilizations, not just processing times."
